This paper discusses the working mechanism of MixUp, which is a popular data augmentation technique used in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the adversarial training aspect of MixUp and introduces a new class of adversarial training schemes called directional adversarial training (DAT). Given that MixUp is a widely used technique in various machine learning applications, it is likely that this paper would be categorized under several sub-categories. However, based on the content of the paper, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
